metatags.twitter:title: Nebraska Enacts Comprehensive Data Privacy Law
metatags.og:title: Nebraska Enacts Comprehensive Data Privacy Law | White & Case LLP
metatags.og:description: On 17 April, 2024, Nebraska Governor Jim Pillen signed into law omnibus Legislative Bill 1074, which includes the Nebraska Data Privacy Act, making Nebraska the seventeenth state to adopt comprehensive data privacy legislation. This signing continues the unprecedented momentum as Nebraska is the fourth state to enact a data privacy law in 2024 alone. The Nebraska Data Privacy Act will take effect on 1 January, 2025. The Nebraska Office of the Attorney General will have exclusive enforcement authority, and there is no private right of action available under this act.

metatags.twitter:title: Nebraska Data Privacy Act: An Overview | Clifford Chance
metatags.twitter:description: On April 17, 2024, Nebraska became the seventeenth state in the U.S. to enact comprehensive data privacy legislation with an omnibus bill headlined by the Nebraska Data Privacy Act (NEDPA). The NEDPA is the fourth law enacted in 2024, adding to the ever-expanding patchwork of state data privacy laws in the US.  The NEDPA takes effect on January 1, 2025.  This article summarizes key provisions of the NEDPA.

metatags.og:title: Nebraska’s Consumer Privacy Law Takes Effect Soon and Targets Businesses Selling Personal Data
metatags.og:description: The Nebraska Data Privacy Act (or NEDPA) becomes effective on January 1, 2025. This relatively short period between signature and effective date left little time for impacted companies to prepare; however, Nebraska’s approach to applicability criteria has cast a specifically tailored net focused on businesses selling personal data of Nebraska residents.
